# Privacy Policy for N-Drobe

**Last updated:** June 07, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how N-Drobe ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and discloses your information when you use our mobile application (the "App").

## 1. Information We Collect and Use

Our App is designed to prioritize your privacy with a strict **"Local-First" architecture**. We do not collect personal information like your name, email address, or phone number unless you explicitly provide it for support. All data is stored locally on your device.

### 1.1. Camera and Photos
**Permission:** `android.permission.CAMERA`, `android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE`, `android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES`
**Usage:** We use your device's camera and photo library to allow you to take pictures of your clothing items or upload existing photos to your virtual wardrobe.
**Storage:** These images are stored exclusively and locally on your device using the Capacitor Filesystem API. **We do not upload your photos to our servers or any cloud storage.**

### 1.2. Location Data
**Permission:** `android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION`, `android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION`
**Usage:** We request access to your location strictly to provide weather-based outfit suggestions.
**Storage:** Your location data is processed temporarily to fetch weather information from a weather provider (Open-Meteo) and is not stored on our servers or shared with third parties for tracking purposes.

### 1.3. Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Image Processing
**Usage:** Our App may use AI features for automatic background removal or clothing categorization.
**Data Handling:** All image processing (including background removal) is performed **locally on your device** (e.g., using WebAssembly). Your photos are never sent to external AI servers or cloud services (such as Google Gemini) for processing. We respect your privacy by ensuring your personal photos never leave your device.

### 1.4. Premium Features and In-App Purchases
**Payment Processing:** Our App offers a one-time Premium upgrade through Google Play In-App Billing.
**Data Handling:** All payment information is processed securely by Google Play. We do not collect, store, or have access to your payment card details.
**What Google Collects:** When you make a purchase, Google Play may collect information as described in their [Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy).
**Purchase Data:** We only store locally on your device whether you have purchased Premium (a simple true/false flag). This is used to unlock features like unlimited wardrobe items and trips.
**No Subscriptions:** Premium is a one-time purchase with no recurring charges.

## 2. Data Storage and Security

*   **Local Storage:** The entirety of your wardrobe data (categories, item lists, photos, planned outfits) is stored locally on your device using `IndexedDB`, `LocalStorage`, or device file storage.
*   **Security:** Since data remains on your device, its security is intrinsically linked to your device's security. We encourage you to use device-level protections like passcodes or biometrics. 

## 3. Third-Party Services

We may use third-party services that collect information used to identify you or to provide specific functionalities (like weather updates or secure payments). Link to privacy policies of third-party service providers used by the app:

*   [Google Play Services](https://policies.google.com/privacy)
*   [Open-Meteo API](https://open-meteo.com/en/features#terms)

## 4. Children’s Privacy

These Services do not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13.

## 5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

## 6. How to Delete Your Data from N-Drobe

**N-Drobe** stores all your data locally on your device. We do not collect or store your data on any remote servers. You can completely delete all data at any time using the methods below.

### What Data Will Be Deleted:
When you delete the app data, the following information will be permanently removed:
- All wardrobe item photos and details
- Trip planning data and packing lists
- Calendar outfit plans
- Personal preferences (name, language, theme)
- Premium purchase status (local flag only - Google Play purchase history is managed separately by Google)

### What Data Will NOT Be Deleted:
- Your Google Play purchase history (if you bought Premium) remains with your Google account and can be restored

### How to Delete Your Data:

**Method 1: Uninstall the App**
Simply uninstall N-Drobe from your device. This will automatically and permanently remove all locally stored data, including photos and wardrobe items. No additional steps required.

**Method 2: Clear App Data (Android)**
1. Open your device Settings
2. Navigate to Apps or Application Manager
3. Find and tap on "N-Drobe"
4. Tap on "Storage" or "Storage & cache"
5. Tap "Clear Data" or "Clear Storage"
6. Confirm the action

This will immediately and permanently delete all data stored by N-Drobe on your device.

**Method 3: In-App Reset**
1. Open N-Drobe app
2. Go to Settings (bottom navigation)
3. Scroll down and tap "Reset Application"
4. Confirm the reset

All data is deleted immediately upon confirmation. There is no retention period - data removal is instant and permanent.

